Thanksgiving Gifts: 2020 Gifts That Say Thanks

Every year, the holidays are a time for gift giving, without a doubt. This year, it seems like we have even more to be thankful for, and even more of a reason to be thankful.

When looking for a gift to say thank you to the special people in your life, you can never go wrong with a gift of sweets, or by pairing sweets with other gifts.

The Nuttery NYis thankful to be able to provide you with alarge selection of treatsto choose from this year! Fromholiday chocolate piesto gift boxes filled withchocolate covered oreoshere are some ideas catered to the people youll likely be gifting to this holiday season.


What to Give Your Thanksgiving Host



This Thanksgiving, dont be the person that brings the fruitcake no one eats and everyone makes fun of. Instead, bring a sweet treat that everyone will be sure to enjoy. We have a few delicious treats sure to make you the hit of any Thanksgiving get-together.


Chocolate Logs

To start,chocolate logsmake an excellent gift for any Thanksgiving host. The best news: they come in a variety of different flavors and patterns, which means there is a chocolate log for any holiday event! They also make great centerpieces, and can serve between 10 and 30 people. Each log is Kosher Certified, as well, so everyone can enjoy them!

Chocolate pralineis a favorite, not only because of its festive, holiday flavor, but also the beautiful white chocolate lace pattern. It is made out of the richest, creamiest chocolate we make, and comes on a beautiful, mahogany wooden tray for serving. Its truly an elegant centerpiece that will elicit oohs and aahs not only from your Thanksgiving host, but from everyone else at the table as well.

Chocolate peanut butteris a classic option and flavor combination, and it comes with a lace pattern also made out of chocolate. Peanut butter is a favorite of so many people, young and old alike, and this tasty log combines that with creamy, rich, thick chocolate.

Chocolate pistachiois a less traditional option, which is part of its allure! It has a unique, beautiful white chocolate pattern. The pistachio is mixed right in with the Parve chocolate on the inside of the log, making for a delicious yet fun holiday treat.

Halvah Zebra logsare one more, super unique option to bring to Thanksgiving. With their rich, sesame flavor, they taste just as good (if not better!) than they look. Its hard to describe the flavor to someone who hasnt experienced it, but its exotic while still tasting smooth and buttery.

Chocolate Tray

If chocolate logs arent your thing, consider a specializedThanksgiving gift tray.The tray is visually stunning and fall appropriate, served on a light, wooden tray and decorated with an autumn orange colored ribbon with the word thankful on it. And every guest at the event will be thankful too, as the gift tray is filled with parve chocolates.

The Thanksgiving gift tray features a two tone roll, which is essentially a white chocolate truffle in log form. It is decorated with delicious dark chocolate details and absolutely just melts in the mouth. It also comes stocked with viennese crunch, a bite size candy made of caramel and chocolate and covered in nuts.In addition, there are jelly rings (Kosher gummies covered in dark chocolate), kava crunch (another delicious candy), cashew patties (freshly roasted cashews clustered together with a creamy, caramel glaze and drizzled with dark chocolate), moccachino (coffee flavored candies), and hazelicious (delicious hazelnut fudge covered in dark chocolate).

Candy and Nut Tray

If that sounds like too much chocolate for you, we also offer afour section Thanksgiving gift traythat substitutes some of the candy with some of our finest speciality nuts. Its a sweet and salty holiday treat everyone will enjoy!When you bring any one of our above mentioned specialty gourmet treats to Thanksgiving, your holiday host will be extra thankful for you this year. They also let you show how thankful you are for having them host! If you want to really express your gratitude, help them with the clean up.

What to Give Your Parents on Thanksgiving

If youre going home for the holidays, you likely already know the struggle associated with finding and bringing your parents the perfect Thanksgiving gift. Your parents have done so much for you in your life, and its only natural to want to show them how thankful you are for them.

Were here to help with that with some gift ideas for your parents this Thanksgiving.For starters, parents always love gifts that remind them that youre always going to be their loving child, which is why personalization can never go wrong.


The best news is that, especially these days, you can personalize just about anything! It all depends on what your parents are into and what you think they would use frequently.

Personalized Picture Frame with an Old Family Photo

One of the best gift ideas that we can think of is apersonalized picture framefilled with an old, restored family photo. While this may take a little time and research, the look on your parents face when they see it is worth more than gold. Parents love the nostalgia factor, and youll love knowing youve made your parents incredibly happy. Its definitely something to be thankful for.

Matching Mugs and Sweet Treats

Matching mugs for your mom and dadare also a great holiday gift option. You can even personalize them further by having their pictures printed directly on them (for an extra special gift idea, use childhood photos of either them or yourself and other siblings).

Pair the photo mugs with a box of chocolates, like theNuttery Signature Chocolate Boxorthe tart boxand it will be a gift theyre sure to love. We think that the tarts are a particularly good choice, as each of the three is handmade, come in a classy box, and pair perfectly with a nice, hot cup of coffee. If they share with you, youll have something to be extra thankful for too!


Gifts for Your Employees on Thanksgiving

If you have employees that you need to buy for this Thanksgiving but arent sure where to start, were here to help make it as easy on you as possible.


Corporate Confection Boxes

Consider giving them aclassic corporate holiday gift box.

Each box is actually an impressive two tiers, with an attractive art deco pattern. Each level is full of a sweet array of gourmet treats, meant to show your sweet, sweet appreciation.The gift box is full of dried apricot and pineapple tidbits, craisins, dried kiwi, cookie poppers, sweet peanuts, coffee candies, and salted cashews, each in their own separate gift boxes. They are compact and will show your employees just how thankful you are for them this holiday season. It has also shown to boost morale, and thats something you can be thankful for too!For smaller companies that can afford a little heftier holiday gift box for their employees, this9 section corporate gift boxis perfect. Each delicious section has its own tasty uniqueness - crispies, butter softies, hazelnut cigars, raspberry fruit, nut mix, BBQ pistachios, sweet peanuts, salted cashews,and salted almonds.Any employee would be thrilled to receive this gift box for any occasion, and when its meant to show how thankful you are for them its even more special. And it just looks impressive!


Smaller Gifts for Other People Youre Thankful For

Just because theyre not your family doesnt mean you cant treat them like they are. This holiday season, show your appreciation tothe other people in your life that youre thankful forby giving them smaller, thoughtful gifts meant to show just how much you care.Gifts like the ones were featuring are perfect for people like teachers, friends, postal workers, and anyone else that youd like to thank for whatever joy or convenience they bring to your life.Its a nice, inexpensive way to show them how important they are to you.


Chocolate Covered Oreos

One of our favorites are theseclassic gift boxes filled with chocolate covered oreos.The festively colored gift boxes are covered in a seasonal, fall pattern, and the chocolate covered oreos inside are not only tasty but also certified kosher! They can even be personalized with a logo for an extra special touch.

Holiday Chocolate Pie

If you need a gift to bring over to your neighbors, give to your coworkers, or bring to your church group or temple holiday event, consider theholiday chocolate pie.The pie is made out of the most rich, decadent, creamy praline chocolate that we make, and decorated by hand with festively colored chocolate decorations (in red and green).Each pie comes on its own beautiful, round tray that you wont have to worry about bringing home with you. These pies make for the perfect holiday centerpiece, no matter wherever you have to go this holiday season. Itll impress everyone, nearly guaranteed.


No matter what you give to show how thankful you are this holiday season, if you give a gift with love and care behind it, its obvious. Have a blessed and happy Thanksgiving!
